<subSubSection pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1436,861,1054]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,903,929]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body fusiform; gnathosoma large, abruptly curved and bent down near base; scapular setae (
<emphasis box="[161,185,945,970]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">sc</emphasis>
) absent; genu II seta absent, paraxial tibial seta (
<emphasis box="[799,817,945,970]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">l’</emphasis>
) absent, empodium divided; anterolateral setae on coxisternum І (
<emphasis box="[330,359,987,1012]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">1b</emphasis>
) absent; opisthosoma with a ridge, setae 
<emphasis box="[843,858,987,1012]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">d</emphasis>
absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1436,861,1054]" box="[208,751,1028,1054]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
